                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/50.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="150" xml:id="d1577fn150">Mutatis mutandis to the American Consul at
                        Hermosillo. The American Chargé d’Affaires at Mexico City advised of
                        contents of the telegram April 14, 1914.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Upon request of diplomatic representative of Germany you will bring to attention
                    of Carranza reported kidnapping by Constitutionalist forces near Guaymas,
                    Sonora, of German subject named <pb facs="1003" n="887" xml:id="pg_887"/> Radke
                    and informally request that he be liberated and allowed to return to his lawful
                    occupation. You will add that German representative further requests this
                    Government to ask that Constitutionalist forces give adequate protection to
                    German subjects within their jurisdiction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
